{"_type":"issue","id":"compile-then-govern-qy7","title":"Productize Governed Second Brain into a public local-first plugin, installer, and marketplace listing","description":"Umbrella epic for turning the Compile-Then-Govern stack into a public, local-first Governed Second Brain that outsiders (esp. the Cowork community) can install and build their own governed, qmd://-cited brain with a tamper-evident audit trail, from inside Claude Code or Cowork. Internal brain + team mode stay untouched. Phases: A public local-MCP plugin (read+write) · B npx installer (egress consent + --index-only) · C marketplace distribution · D cross-link/thesis-fold/tracking. Plus standalone MUST-FIX beads (audit-anchor HIGH, egress mode, installer security, gsb.lock.json).","notes":"GitHub: intent-solutions-io/governed-second-brain#1 — https://github.com/intent-solutions-io/governed-second-brain/issues/1. MIRROR RULE: bd-sync handles fan-out — `bd-sync note compile-then-govern-qy7` and `bd-sync close compile-then-govern-qy7` mirror to GH and Plane automatically.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"jeremylongshore@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-06-16T23:10:42Z","created_by":"jeremylongshore","updated_at":"2026-06-16T23:13:16Z","labels":["plugin","productization"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
